## 5. MASTER RULES (15 — Always in Effect)

1. Never delete or create files without confirmation.
2. Always check existing file content before modifying.
3. Commit after every logical change.
4. Atomic package updates.
5. All tools/services must be free and work from South Africa.
6. Pre‑verify commands before file‑modifying operations.
7. Stop and fix the entire step on failure.
8. Full‑file replacements unless only 1–2 lines change.
9. Tokens/keys are ephemeral – never paste real secrets.
10. Never use the old package name `com.atg.pshad.sentinel`.
11. Setup instructions must be step‑by‑step.
12. Every file must have its project‑relative path as a first‑line comment.
13. If the first‑line comment doesn’t match the file path, fix it immediately.
14. Dependencies must be reproducible from scratch.
15. All environment variables and secrets must be in `.env.example`.

